---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — NTE Codex" description="How NTE Codex handles cookies, analytics and advertising.">
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Last updated: 2026-05-10</p>

  <div class="prose-game max-w-prose">
    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Google Analytics 4 records page visits, referrer, device, and rough geolocation. Data is aggregated.</li>
      <li><strong>Advertising:</strong> Once Google AdSense is approved, ad serving and frequency capping use cookies. AdSense may personalize ads based on your prior browsing across sites.</li>
      <li><strong>No accounts.</strong> We do not have user logins or comments, so we never collect emails, passwords, or profile data.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      The cookie banner stores a single localStorage flag (<code>cookie-ok</code>) so we
      don't show it twice. AdSense and GA4 set their own cookies when you continue browsing.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      EU/UK users can opt out of personalised ads via the standard
      <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">YourOnlineChoices</a>
      page. California residents can request data deletion via <a href="/contact">contact</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party services</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Google Analytics — see <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Google's privacy policy</a>.</li>
      <li>Google AdSense — see <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Google ads policy</a>.</li>
      <li>Cloudflare — used for hosting and DDoS mitigation. See <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Cloudflare privacy</a>.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
